{"TopicId":193525,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Expanded Launch Abort Systems","CreatedByName":"Bar27262","CreatedById":141348,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T15:04:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Bar27262","CreatedById":141348,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T15:04:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that the KSP 2 developers should add in more Launch Abort systems that could protect the life of the crew should something happen.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe normal launch abort system is a good choice but I think there could be slightly improved options. Perhaps there could be ejection seats (one way to possibly do this is have a MK2/MK3 cockpit with ejection seats already coded in that can be activated separately.) and also a system similar to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E or reaction wheels that you could put on a spacecraft that can automatically activate the launch abort system if there is favorable realistic\u00A0conditions.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis could save a lot of peoples kerbals life in career mode, even more so if you make ejection seats start out as a starting technology. You could go for progressively better ones as technology goes on. Come to discuss and let me know what you think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T18:03:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts a good idea. I\u0027ve used the ejection mod before and it did save my Kerbals from my poor flying skills.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T20:42:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbals are immortal. They\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Earen\u0027t\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Erequired\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T21:31:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588365757\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbals are immortal. They\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Earen\u0027t\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Erequired\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u00A0They don\u0027t age, but they sure aren\u0027t immortal!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dirkidirk","CreatedById":200064,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T21:34:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588365757\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbals are immortal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwho said that they were immortal, they clearly die from\u00A0explosions and high speed impacts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588365757\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidCosmos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, VoidCosmos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Earen\u0027t\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Erequired\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwho said that they are required?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lewie","CreatedById":203745,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-02T02:57:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just noticed this, but the thrust at sea level for the stock escape system is 666.6 m/s. Coincidence or not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T02:00:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588388258\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203745\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lewie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Lewie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just noticed this, but the thrust at sea level for the stock escape system is 666.6 m/s. Coincidence or not?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpoopy\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}